TY  - JOUR
AU  - Perry, Martin K.
AU  - Groff, Robert H.
T1  - Resale Price Maintenance and Forward Integration into a Monopolistically Competitive Industry
PY  - 1985
Y1  - 1985/11/01
DO  - 10.2307/1885684
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 100
IS  - 4
SP  - 1293
EP  - 1311
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - In this paper we adopt the CES model of product differentiation for the downstream stage of the industry. With an upstream monopolist we first show that resale price maintenance is equivalent to forward integration and that both increase profits. Then we demonstrate that forward integration by an upstream monopolist will reduce welfare for the industry. Prices fall with forward integration, but the integrating firm contracts the number of downstream subsidiaries so drastically that the reduced diversity more than offsets the gains from lower prices.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1885684
ER  - 



